[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
I move past him and walk fast to the stairs.[p]
So Khai already knew how horrible i was at work today and here i thought i could wait until i'm at least half decent to tell him.[p]
I jumped into bed with disappointment filled in my heart.[p]
Mother...she probably already knew it too. And yet she didn't come or say anything. Was she...ashamed of me?[p]
Rolling in bed, i found a gift on my desk. There's a cute hair piece inside with a note "Thank you for trying your best on the first day" with a handwriting that i couldn't recognize. Maybe it was Khai's? Silly big brother. And yet i got mad at you...[p]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
It's been three days since An started working as an internship nurse and everything was chaotic.[p]
Everywhere she went, people looked at her as if she's a criminal, some patients even yelled at her and not allowing her to take care of them.[p]
The situation was so bad Kai had to assign her to patients with heavy illness and low income, those who were desperately in need of a personal nurse yet could never afford one.[p]
The job was harsh but at least AN finally had a place to start her dream now.[p]
The old lady with Ahzheimer, the kid with blood cancer... An took care and tried to be friend with all of them and they slowly became more open with her.[p]
Despite all her lack of experience which usually ended up by her getting scolded by Kai.[p]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
Of all the patients, Lan was the one one who took the most time from her.[p]
She's a chef girl who was about An's age with breast cancer. [p]
She took chemotherapy and so many drug therapies on a daily basic yet her fiance who was also a chef couldn't come to take care of her too regular since her fiance who he had to work hard in order to pay hospital fees.[p]
The therapy sessions were long and painful so An always stayed next to An, talked with her and made sure she could return to her hospital room safe and sound.[p]
[_tb_end_text]

[tb_start_text mode=1 ]
One day, Lan suddenly collapsed and they had to rush putting her in operation. As Lan was unconcious, An started crying and Kai locked her out of the operation room, asking another nurse to assist him.[p]
After the operation over and Lan was fine, Kai came out of the operation room scolding An for how she cried.[p]
Within this job she wasn't allowed to look panic or helpless because that would make the patient panic too.[p]
You had to be the place for them to lean on, especially in dangerous situations. In between her tears, An appologized.[p]
She was so worried about Lan she couldn't do any better. Behind the door, Lan saw everything and smiled.[p]
From that day, they became friends.[p]
Lan told An about her life. How she met her fiance Minh when they were both orphans in the same orphanage.[p]
How they dreamed of having a restaurant and family together. How they worked so hard to get it.[p]
How cancer might have taken a lot of things away from her but in the end she will win.[p]
[_tb_end_text]

